title: For Sale:  wow!! really??
postcontent:
How is it that the majority of people on arms list think their shit doesn't stink?  In my experience with people on this site I have encountered some of the rudest people.  

Now I know that we all lead busy lives.  I know that sometimes you contact people on the sight and sometimes people contact you.  And it is because you have either listed an item for sale or trade or are interested in a item for sale or trade.  But why be rude about it?  

In dealing with people here I have been told to go to hell because we were off by $10 on what each of us thought was the fair price.  I have been asked to give someone a call after I have inquired about their item.  During the call I have either been hung up on or been told that I do not know what the f I am talking about.  Now I admit I do not know everything but I do have a better then good understanding of this topic.  But when people get upset because you are trying to get info about what they have or they just flat hang up is unbelievable to me.  Then you have my favorite.   The email.  Either some one asks about your item or you about theirs and ultimately someone asks for more pics.  Or they would like a few more questions answered to determine the value of the item.  I take the time to take a few more pics and answer their questions and then that's it.  Never to be heard from again and this is after 4  - 8 email exchanges.

I personally do not understand why it is so hard to be nice.  You have posted something on the site or you are inquiring about something on the site.  Be nice, be polite, be friendly.  It isn't that hard to not waste others time.
